The paper focuses on the security concerns of transactive energy systems, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the need for distributed computing and platforms for simulation, which falls under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of blockchain technology, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the weaknesses of centralized systems and the need for decentralized solutions, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
